article.headline: New Orleans 103, Belhaven 69
article.story: TYLER, Texas (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored 28 points to lead New Orleans to a 103-69 victory over Belhaven on Saturday in a home game played in East Texas because of Hurricane Katrina. Jamie McNeilly added 18 points for New Orleans (1-0), which has been displaced since Katrina swamped the Gulf Coast in late August. The Privateers will play two more games in Tyler before its first campus game Dec. 31. James Parlow scored 14 points and Shawn Malloy and Wayne Williams added 10 for New Orleans, which scored 47 points off 30 Belhaven turnovers. McCalebb was 10 of 18 from the field and McNeilly hit four of five 3-pointers. Bobby Johnson led Belhaven (1-3) with 19 points.
